text: Georgetown County is a county in the U.S. state of South Carolina. As of the 2020 census, 63,404 people lived there. Its county seat is Georgetown. The county was formed in 1769. It is named for George III of the United Kingdom. == References == Category:18th-century establishments in South Carolina Category:1769 establishments in the Thirteen Colonies Category:South Carolina counties
